-- EU Forecasts German Growth Rate of 1.2% This Year, 1.6% in 2011, Welt Says
-- Cornelius Rahn
-- 2010-07-31T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-31/eu-forecasts-german-growth-rate-of-1-2-this-year-1-6-in-2011-welt-says.html

          
          
             The European Commission forecasts
that Germany’s economy will grow 1.2 percent this year, compared
with a 1.4 percent projection by the German government,  Die Welt 
reported, citing  Marco Buti , the commission’s head of economics.  
 The European Union will grow 1 percent this year, and
German growth will reach 1.6 percent in 2011, the newspaper
cited Buti as saying.  
